jchrest.domainSpecifics

Class Fixation

  • java.lang.Object
    • jchrest.domainSpecifics.Fixation
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AheadOfAgentFixation, AttackDefenseFixation, CentralFixation, GlobalStrategyFixation, HypothesisDiscriminationFixation, MovementFixation, PeripheralItemFixation, PeripheralSquareFixation, SalientManFixation, SalientObjectFixation

    public abstract class Fixation
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the result of a Perceiver associated with a Chrest model focusing on a Square in a jchrest.lib.Scene. A Fixation has two time variables. The first denotes when the Square that is to be focused on by a Perceiver associated with a Chrest model has been selected (time decided upon). The second denotes the time that #this is to be performed, i.e. the time that the Perceiver associated with a Chrest model actually focuses on the Square selected. These times can vary from one type of Fixation to another and so should be set accordingly. A Fixation also stores the jchrest.lib.Scene that #this was performed in context of, the x and y coordinates of the Square fixated on in the jchrest.lib.Scene and the jchrest.lib.SceneObject present on the Square fixated on. The instance variables of #this that store this information should only be set when #this is actually performed. By default, these instance variables are all set to null.

      • perform

        public boolean perform(Scene scene,
                       int time)
        Used to perform the fixation that #this represents on the jchrest.lib.Scene specified using the concrete implementation of #this#make(jchrest.lib.Scene, int). If the fixation that #this represents is successfully made, then the scene this fixation is made in context of will be set to the jchrest.lib.Scene specified as a parameter to this method, the x and y coordinates fixated on will be set to the result of invoking Square.getColumn() and Square.getRow() on the Square fixated on and the object seen will be set to the jchrest.lib.SceneObject that is present on the Square that #this is performed on.
        Parameters:
        scene - The jchrest.lib.Scene that #this should be performed in context of.
        time -
        Returns:
        Boolean.TRUE if all the following are true, otherwise Boolean.FALSE is returned:
        • The time specified as a parameter, i.e. the time that #this is to be performed, is later than or equal to #this#getPerformanceTime().
        • The concrete implementation of {@link #this#doFixation( jchrest.architecture.Chrest, jchrest.lib.Scene, int)} returns an {@link jchrest.lib.ItemSquarePattern}, i.e. {@link #this} was successfully performed.

      • make

        public abstract Square make(Scene scene,
                            int time)
        This method should not be invoked directly to make #this since it will not be guaranteed that the instance variables of #this pertaining to its performance will be set by the concrete implementation. Neither can it be guaranteed that the jchrest.lib.Scene that #this is made in context of is the jchrest.lib.Scene that previous Fixations in the same set have been made in context of. Use #this#perform(jchrest.lib.Scene, int) instead.
        Parameters:
        scene - The jchrest.lib.Scene that #this is to be made in context of.
        time - The time #this is to be made, in milliseconds.
        Returns:
        A Square denoting where the Perceiver associated with the Chrest model making #this should focus its attention on (coordinates specified should be relative to the coordinates of the scene specified rather than the domain that the scene represents. If #this is not made successfully, null should be returned.
